    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1939-06-23T18:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1939-06-23T18:00:00-05:00" n="608"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d608">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">838.51/3804: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Minister in Haiti</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Mayer</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1939-06-23T19:00:00-04:00"
                            >June 23, 1939—7 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>64. Your 84, June 12, 9 a.m. and 88, June 16, 9 a.m.<note n="22"
                        xml:id="d608fn22">Neither printed.</note> Mr. Francis White of the Foreign
                    Bondholders Protective Council informed the Department that the Council had
                    discussed the Haitian note requesting a moratorium communicated to him by de la
                    Rue and agreed that the Haitian request was reasonable. The Council expressed
                    appreciation of the offer of the Haitian Government to devote any budgetary
                    surplus as might result from the fiscal year 1939–1940 with the exception of
                    such extraordinary appropriations as might be authorized by the Fiscal
                    Representative, to the amortization of the 1922 Loan.</p>
                <p>You are requested at your discretion to acknowledge the receipt of the note of
                    June 12 from the Haitian Minister of Foreign Affairs and to state that you are
                    authorized, and authorization is hereby given you, to sign a supplemental
                    executive agreement extending the Accord <pb facs="0657" n="649" xml:id="pg_649"
                    /> of July 1, 1938 for one additional year from September 30, 1939. In your note
                    of acknowledgment you should of course refer to the undertaking of the Haitian
                    Government referred to in the last sentence of the paragraph next above.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
